Date: 16 Dec 2005
From: William Karesh <wkaresh@wcs.org>

Field teams just out of forest. After thorough investigation, no ape
carcasses found and no evidence of animal mortalities. Initial reports were
thought to be likely due to poaching.
--
William B Karesh, DVM, Director
Field Veterinary Program
Wildlife Conservation Society
2300 Southern Blvd
Bronx, NY 10460 USA
<wkaresh@wcs.org>
[We appreciate Dr Karesh's rapid follow-up report. - Mod.TG]
